WEBVTT

00:00:29.382 --> 00:00:32.264
Welcome back to our ocean studio of the

00:00:32.423 --> 00:00:33.164
Yahowah vlog.

00:00:33.204 --> 00:00:34.344
I'm your host, Craig Winn.

00:00:34.365 --> 00:00:36.365
And of course, this handsome fellow here,

00:00:36.405 --> 00:00:37.465
he is Wookie.

00:00:38.066 --> 00:00:42.027
We're delighted to be here this morning

00:00:42.987 --> 00:00:44.908
because of the storms that passed through

00:00:44.948 --> 00:00:45.648
here yesterday.

00:00:45.688 --> 00:00:48.228
It was a once in, well,

00:00:48.249 --> 00:00:50.189
maybe even a lifetime kind of an event

00:00:50.448 --> 00:00:51.570
here for the U.S.

00:00:51.630 --> 00:00:52.450
Virgin Islands.

00:00:53.450 --> 00:00:56.191
I think what we got was the telltale

00:00:56.331 --> 00:00:58.012
end of that storm.

00:00:58.752 --> 00:01:02.476
bomb storm that wreaked so much havoc

00:01:02.578 --> 00:01:03.819
along the East Coast.

00:01:03.899 --> 00:01:05.701
It wasn't particularly cold.

00:01:06.802 --> 00:01:09.106
Temperatures were still in the high

00:01:09.206 --> 00:01:09.908
seventies,

00:01:10.347 --> 00:01:11.870
even low eighties throughout the day.

00:01:12.290 --> 00:01:14.213
But oh my, was it blustery.

00:01:14.313 --> 00:01:15.215
It was kind of like the

00:01:15.995 --> 00:01:18.617
prelim to a tropical storm,

00:01:18.897 --> 00:01:20.397
but of course the wrong temperature for

00:01:20.417 --> 00:01:21.757
that and wrong time of year.

00:01:23.058 --> 00:01:24.198
And the rain,

00:01:24.459 --> 00:01:26.519
while consistent throughout the day,

00:01:26.558 --> 00:01:28.760
wasn't torrential as it would normally be.

00:01:28.799 --> 00:01:30.540
But a storm coming out of the west

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:32.161
is unusual for us,

00:01:33.221 --> 00:01:34.762
as well as a storm that is,

00:01:34.781 --> 00:01:35.361
you know,

00:01:35.402 --> 00:01:37.582
that intense during this time of year.

00:01:38.322 --> 00:01:40.643
So obviously we were hunkered down

00:01:41.424 --> 00:01:44.465
yesterday and delighted to be back out in

00:01:44.484 --> 00:01:45.625
our ocean studio and

00:01:45.924 --> 00:01:47.025
broadcasting today.

00:01:48.325 --> 00:01:49.025
I will tell you, though,

00:01:49.046 --> 00:01:50.466
that I'm coming to you with a heavy

00:01:50.507 --> 00:01:50.807
heart.

00:01:51.606 --> 00:01:55.789
I am grateful that Yahowah held off in

00:01:55.828 --> 00:01:58.349
having me examine the darkest episode of

00:01:58.489 --> 00:02:03.031
my dear King's wonderful and brilliant

00:02:03.070 --> 00:02:05.331
life, at least up to this point,

00:02:06.331 --> 00:02:08.052
to this particular time.

00:02:09.073 --> 00:02:10.334
I am now covering

00:02:11.334 --> 00:02:12.955
The episode of Bathsheba,

00:02:13.856 --> 00:02:20.062
which is tragic in all of its intensity,

00:02:20.163 --> 00:02:22.284
all of its permeations,

00:02:22.324 --> 00:02:26.528
everything that Dowd said and did pursuant

00:02:26.549 --> 00:02:27.890
to this was just horrendous.

00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:32.382
And I realized that, you know,

00:02:32.401 --> 00:02:36.264
that Dowd was an exceptional man for

00:02:36.384 --> 00:02:37.705
forty-eight years of his life,

00:02:38.006 --> 00:02:41.628
from eight years old when Yahowah first

00:02:42.649 --> 00:02:44.871
placed his Ruwach spirit on him and

00:02:44.911 --> 00:02:46.972
anointed him Mashyach,

00:02:47.592 --> 00:02:50.074
to the time that he was fifty-six years

00:02:50.213 --> 00:02:50.435
old.

00:02:51.115 --> 00:02:52.996
He lived his life in the center of

00:02:53.415 --> 00:02:55.317
Yah's brilliant spotlight.

00:02:55.576 --> 00:02:57.318
He was bold.

00:02:57.358 --> 00:02:58.478
He was courageous.

00:02:58.557 --> 00:03:00.218
He was articulate.

00:03:00.258 --> 00:03:01.759
He was a great prophet.

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.700
He was a great defender of his people.

00:03:04.681 --> 00:03:08.242
He was engaged in doing wonderful things.

00:03:08.502 --> 00:03:10.204
And then it all fell apart.

00:03:11.503 --> 00:03:12.365
And when it fell apart,

00:03:13.046 --> 00:03:15.829
It crashed with intensity and reminds us

00:03:16.269 --> 00:03:18.550
somewhat of Moshe's experience,

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:22.012
although Moshe's crash and burn came much

00:03:22.513 --> 00:03:23.832
sooner than Dowd's.

00:03:24.013 --> 00:03:29.676
Moshe left, as we know, Mitsraym.

00:03:31.486 --> 00:03:34.127
And around the time he was forty years

00:03:34.247 --> 00:03:34.467
old,

00:03:34.707 --> 00:03:37.108
tried to help in an act of courage,

00:03:37.127 --> 00:03:38.288
really, in his youth,

00:03:38.508 --> 00:03:39.489
tried to help his people,

00:03:39.989 --> 00:03:42.610
defending them against the cruelty of the

00:03:42.689 --> 00:03:43.530
caste system,

00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:46.930
the religion and politics of Egypt.

00:03:47.691 --> 00:03:52.111
And then when Yahowah called him back at

00:03:52.611 --> 00:03:56.252
eighty years old and he re-engaged in

00:03:57.293 --> 00:03:57.552
this,

00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:01.213
doing, you know,

00:04:01.533 --> 00:04:04.318
reluctantly going back into Mitsraym to

00:04:05.079 --> 00:04:08.462
relieve his people from the tyranny of

00:04:10.164 --> 00:04:11.186
civilization, really.

00:04:13.068 --> 00:04:14.871
He didn't last a year.

00:04:15.867 --> 00:04:18.088
in this new role as the liberator of

00:04:18.129 --> 00:04:20.050
his people before he had a meltdown and

00:04:21.411 --> 00:04:23.411
actually cursed Yahowah for putting him in

00:04:23.451 --> 00:04:24.172
this position,

00:04:24.211 --> 00:04:25.673
saying that no one could do this job,

00:04:25.713 --> 00:04:26.632
and he asked God to kill him.

00:04:27.973 --> 00:04:29.735
He went through the paces from that point

00:04:29.855 --> 00:04:29.995
on,

00:04:31.095 --> 00:04:33.716
doing some things that were fairly

00:04:33.857 --> 00:04:37.358
extraordinary as it relates to getting his

00:04:37.418 --> 00:04:38.658
people to the Promised Land,

00:04:38.678 --> 00:04:40.240
but he was just going through the paces

00:04:40.279 --> 00:04:44.762
from that point, having really given up.

00:04:46.755 --> 00:04:47.916
on everything.

00:04:47.997 --> 00:04:51.779
So it is an exceedingly difficult job that

00:04:51.959 --> 00:04:52.821
Dowd was placed in,

00:04:53.641 --> 00:04:54.882
as Moshe was placed in.

00:04:56.324 --> 00:05:00.927
Dowd persevered longer than Moshe by a

00:05:00.987 --> 00:05:01.548
long shot,

00:05:02.870 --> 00:05:05.432
and both of them much longer than I

00:05:05.471 --> 00:05:08.173
have in this spotlight as well.

00:05:08.233 --> 00:05:10.016
So I have some empathy for them and

00:05:10.036 --> 00:05:11.317
know how difficult the job is.

00:05:12.137 --> 00:05:13.819
But reading

00:05:14.449 --> 00:05:17.831
really how far God went to extinguish his

00:05:17.891 --> 00:05:20.613
light.

00:05:20.874 --> 00:05:21.353
It's hurtful.

00:05:22.574 --> 00:05:23.735
It turns the stomach.

00:05:24.516 --> 00:05:26.137
And ultimately,

00:05:27.017 --> 00:05:29.060
we know that Yahowah had a plan.

00:05:29.319 --> 00:05:32.201
And it's one of the most ingenious aspects

00:05:32.262 --> 00:05:33.182
of the whole story,

00:05:33.283 --> 00:05:35.543
one that I had not seen until this

00:05:35.665 --> 00:05:38.666
past week, which is that Yahowah...

00:05:39.723 --> 00:05:44.408
had a means of keeping his story and

00:05:44.488 --> 00:05:49.233
his intent and his people on track for

00:05:49.374 --> 00:05:51.355
their reconciliation in the end,

00:05:53.319 --> 00:05:55.100
which did not interfere with free will,

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:56.721
didn't interfere with the

00:06:00.346 --> 00:06:03.247
normal progression of time and therefore

00:06:03.307 --> 00:06:05.447
didn't infringe on cause and effect,

00:06:05.947 --> 00:06:08.528
didn't make a great show so that the

00:06:08.588 --> 00:06:10.889
choice to know him or reject him would

00:06:10.949 --> 00:06:13.889
remain as it has always been,

00:06:14.649 --> 00:06:19.790
and gave him the opportunity to do as

00:06:19.850 --> 00:06:20.992
he said he would,

00:06:21.031 --> 00:06:23.651
which is to work everything through people

00:06:23.932 --> 00:06:25.492
and not do anything alone.

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:28.682
God found a way to do that,

00:06:28.762 --> 00:06:30.824
and it was actually hinted at for the

00:06:30.884 --> 00:06:31.904
first time.

00:06:32.264 --> 00:06:32.425
Well,

00:06:32.444 --> 00:06:35.987
the nature of these people was addressed

00:06:36.468 --> 00:06:38.629
in the greater and lesser luminary,

00:06:38.990 --> 00:06:41.312
and again in the trees of knowledge and

00:06:41.351 --> 00:06:42.692
of lives in the garden.

00:06:44.595 --> 00:06:44.675
And

00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:48.874
Their story was also told with the parting

00:06:49.413 --> 00:06:52.255
discussion that Yahowah had about what we

00:06:52.276 --> 00:06:55.519
are to do relative to our fathers and

00:06:55.559 --> 00:06:59.802
mothers going forward and our exit from

00:06:59.841 --> 00:07:00.242
the garden.

00:07:01.798 --> 00:07:04.838
the first character that would be deployed

00:07:04.899 --> 00:07:07.699
in this way is a fellow whose name

00:07:07.759 --> 00:07:10.019
actually identifies his purpose.

00:07:10.360 --> 00:07:13.019
That would be Chanowk, known as Enoch.

00:07:13.459 --> 00:07:15.300
And the name means that he was trained,

00:07:15.380 --> 00:07:18.480
that he was prepared, that he was devoted,

00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:21.382
and then he was deployed to intervene in

00:07:21.401 --> 00:07:23.341
the way that he did and then removed

00:07:24.163 --> 00:07:27.543
so that he could be dispatched and

00:07:27.583 --> 00:07:30.684
intervene at other times along the

00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.821
progression of time and events and places

00:07:36.860 --> 00:07:37.300
and people.

00:07:38.120 --> 00:07:40.101
Uh, there is one man and one woman,

00:07:40.701 --> 00:07:42.382
um, for this calling, uh,

00:07:43.221 --> 00:07:45.942
and they become as instrumental in the

00:07:46.043 --> 00:07:49.064
overall story as do the key characters

00:07:49.124 --> 00:07:51.843
like Moshe and Dowd.

00:07:51.863 --> 00:07:53.805
So it is, uh,

00:07:53.824 --> 00:07:54.704
it is quite a story, uh,

00:07:55.464 --> 00:07:57.225
and the way that God goes about, uh,

00:07:57.245 --> 00:07:59.086
telling it and, um,

00:08:01.416 --> 00:08:03.197
bringing it to our attention keeping it on

00:08:03.237 --> 00:08:05.939
track is something that um i have just

00:08:05.980 --> 00:08:09.182
come to appreciate and and had i not

00:08:10.382 --> 00:08:12.805
been introduced to the final word picture

00:08:12.845 --> 00:08:15.947
which is a story we're about to complete

00:08:16.007 --> 00:08:19.028
at least in the uh in the uh

00:08:19.108 --> 00:08:20.930
story of the thirty first marshall by

00:08:20.990 --> 00:08:23.411
itself we will complete that uh later

00:08:23.451 --> 00:08:24.913
today uh but

00:08:26.363 --> 00:08:28.586
Had I not been introduced to it this

00:08:28.646 --> 00:08:28.985
way,

00:08:29.206 --> 00:08:31.588
seeing how Yahowah resolved the problem of

00:08:31.649 --> 00:08:34.331
his son's waywardness,

00:08:34.750 --> 00:08:36.371
it would have been a tough thing to

00:08:36.412 --> 00:08:38.594
recover from because my life is devoted to

00:08:38.653 --> 00:08:42.177
restoring Dowd's reputation with his

00:08:42.216 --> 00:08:43.197
people and with the world.

00:08:43.918 --> 00:08:46.821
And without knowing how God managed to

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:49.442
restore his relationship with Dowd once he

00:08:49.482 --> 00:08:51.124
crashed and burned, well,

00:08:51.144 --> 00:08:52.725
that would have been a difficult thing to

00:08:52.784 --> 00:08:53.306
do.

00:08:53.405 --> 00:08:53.586
Yeah.

00:08:54.900 --> 00:08:56.481
I'm telling you all of this so that

00:08:56.501 --> 00:09:00.482
you have some sense of my mindset as

00:09:00.562 --> 00:09:01.423
I do these programs.

00:09:01.462 --> 00:09:04.543
I try to be as transparent as possible.

00:09:04.583 --> 00:09:05.764
It's one of the reasons we do these

00:09:05.803 --> 00:09:08.184
programs here in our Ocean Studio,

00:09:08.225 --> 00:09:10.485
because you can see they're obviously

00:09:10.525 --> 00:09:12.905
being live streamed and that this is a

00:09:13.365 --> 00:09:15.966
stream of consciousness for you and that

00:09:16.447 --> 00:09:18.947
I'm trying to be as open and

00:09:20.028 --> 00:09:22.556
as vulnerable, really, as is possible,

00:09:22.937 --> 00:09:24.380
and doing these programs in this

00:09:24.441 --> 00:09:26.886
environment, in this manner, with you.

00:09:30.381 --> 00:09:32.384
Should you read something in my demeanor

00:09:32.443 --> 00:09:34.504
that is slightly different than what you

00:09:34.544 --> 00:09:35.826
have seen previously,

00:09:36.206 --> 00:09:37.047
you'll know what it is.

00:09:37.086 --> 00:09:39.149
And we have a Jack Spaniard that is

00:09:39.469 --> 00:09:40.909
visiting the set at the moment.

00:09:41.530 --> 00:09:43.591
And I do not like them,

00:09:43.631 --> 00:09:44.232
Sam I am.

00:09:44.312 --> 00:09:49.256
So if you see him swing back by,

00:09:49.297 --> 00:09:51.217
you will see me try to whack him

00:09:51.337 --> 00:09:53.539
out of the way.

00:09:54.480 --> 00:09:56.042
I have been bitten by them in the

00:09:56.101 --> 00:09:58.344
past, and it did not go well.

00:09:59.982 --> 00:10:00.222
All right,

00:10:00.263 --> 00:10:03.644
so now returning to the eighth Mizmowr,

00:10:04.025 --> 00:10:05.986
which is the Song of Dowd.

00:10:06.927 --> 00:10:09.288
While it bears the number eight currently,

00:10:09.688 --> 00:10:12.150
we're really not in a position to know

00:10:12.211 --> 00:10:15.592
whether or not it was eight in the

00:10:15.732 --> 00:10:20.115
order that he revealed or really when we

00:10:20.155 --> 00:10:23.879
now have a squatter that we can use

00:10:24.938 --> 00:10:25.659
should we need it.

00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:26.961
All right, so...

00:10:27.821 --> 00:10:29.101
We don't know really what the order they

00:10:29.121 --> 00:10:29.722
were revealed.

00:10:30.243 --> 00:10:33.345
They could have been revealed at a very

00:10:33.384 --> 00:10:33.905
different order.

00:10:33.946 --> 00:10:36.868
I'm not able to do with the Dowd's

00:10:37.828 --> 00:10:40.350
Mizmowr what I was able to do with

00:10:40.831 --> 00:10:41.551
the Quran,

00:10:41.691 --> 00:10:44.153
which took that jumbled mess and reordered

00:10:44.192 --> 00:10:46.575
it chronologically by putting into the

00:10:46.615 --> 00:10:48.976
context of Muhammad's life through the

00:10:49.096 --> 00:10:49.677
Hadith.

00:10:50.898 --> 00:10:51.558
Because it's...

00:10:54.370 --> 00:10:58.932
Dowd talks about topics in a way that

00:10:59.292 --> 00:11:02.634
he literally telescopes time.

00:11:03.333 --> 00:11:06.115
The Wookie is about to push my Coke

00:11:06.255 --> 00:11:08.035
off the end of the table here.

00:11:08.135 --> 00:11:09.116
That would be another mess.

00:11:09.616 --> 00:11:15.220
So he literally telescopes time in his

00:11:15.399 --> 00:11:15.899
Mizmowr,

00:11:16.220 --> 00:11:18.182
so they're very difficult to anchor in

00:11:18.221 --> 00:11:18.581
time.

00:11:18.621 --> 00:11:21.182
So we don't know when each was revealed,

00:11:21.202 --> 00:11:22.923
but they all tell us something that is

00:11:22.984 --> 00:11:23.624
extraordinary.

00:11:23.644 --> 00:11:28.746
And I think that many of them now

00:11:29.746 --> 00:11:33.850
show the benefit of the intervention that

00:11:34.029 --> 00:11:36.410
we had with him some three thousand years

00:11:36.471 --> 00:11:38.011
ago so that he would recognize.

00:11:39.113 --> 00:11:40.533
who he was, what his purpose was,

00:11:40.573 --> 00:11:41.355
what his calling was,

00:11:41.394 --> 00:11:43.096
what he must achieve in life,

00:11:43.135 --> 00:11:44.817
and why it was important that he reconcile

00:11:44.836 --> 00:11:47.099
his relationship with Yahowah that he had

00:11:47.158 --> 00:11:51.363
fractured through the Bathsheba incident.

00:11:51.383 --> 00:11:52.263
So this continues.

00:11:52.783 --> 00:11:55.186
Therefore, you have made him,

00:11:55.365 --> 00:11:56.547
speaking of mortal man,

00:11:56.667 --> 00:11:57.847
somewhat diminished,

00:11:58.227 --> 00:12:00.389
withholding something.

00:12:03.350 --> 00:12:06.272
And this is really interesting, of course,

00:12:06.312 --> 00:12:08.033
withholding something from God.

00:12:08.552 --> 00:12:11.274
And yet you surround and enveloped him

00:12:11.735 --> 00:12:12.955
with honor and respect,

00:12:12.995 --> 00:12:15.275
with an abundance of riches and with a

00:12:15.336 --> 00:12:17.937
powerful presence and a glorious reward

00:12:17.956 --> 00:12:18.518
and Kabowd ,

00:12:18.857 --> 00:12:20.899
along with the most appealing attributes,

00:12:20.958 --> 00:12:23.779
valuable qualities and useful aptitudes.

00:12:24.559 --> 00:12:29.725
This is such a powerful statement and so

00:12:29.764 --> 00:12:31.446
remarkably insightful.

00:12:32.047 --> 00:12:34.109
It's the same conclusion that I have

00:12:34.528 --> 00:12:34.970
drawn,

00:12:35.330 --> 00:12:37.951
but the difference is I drew it after

00:12:38.753 --> 00:12:40.794
considering everything Yahowah had to say

00:12:40.934 --> 00:12:41.676
and then...

00:12:42.515 --> 00:12:44.298
deducing what I thought were the most

00:12:44.378 --> 00:12:45.879
rational conclusions from it.

00:12:46.740 --> 00:12:47.400
In this case,

00:12:47.541 --> 00:12:49.623
Dowd was inspired as a prophet to state

00:12:49.643 --> 00:12:50.543
this emphatically.

00:12:51.225 --> 00:12:53.947
So it does validate some things that I

00:12:54.008 --> 00:12:57.471
have shared with you over this past year

00:12:57.510 --> 00:12:59.572
through the Yahowah vlog and through the past

00:12:59.633 --> 00:13:02.855
twenty-four years through the Yaada Yahowah

00:13:02.916 --> 00:13:03.317
series.

00:13:04.682 --> 00:13:06.003
And should you wish to follow along,

00:13:06.383 --> 00:13:07.823
we are concluding.

00:13:07.884 --> 00:13:10.945
We're in really the final episodes of what

00:13:10.985 --> 00:13:15.548
will be our comprehensive journey through

00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:15.927
this.

00:13:15.988 --> 00:13:18.509
This was volume one of the series called

00:13:18.589 --> 00:13:19.450
Coming Home.

00:13:20.309 --> 00:13:21.030
It's a voice.

00:13:21.671 --> 00:13:23.091
And it is...

00:13:26.410 --> 00:13:29.812
my recommendation for everyone to read it.

00:13:29.832 --> 00:13:32.835
I think you'll gain so much more from

00:13:32.875 --> 00:13:33.695
it, reading it.

