Now there is an advantage of listening to

00:13:35.436 --> 00:13:39.418
it because I augment the text and make

00:13:39.437 --> 00:13:41.239
commentary as I am right now,

00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:44.421
way beyond anything that I have written.

00:13:44.461 --> 00:13:46.162
And I bring the text up to date

00:13:46.201 --> 00:13:46.883
in the sense that

00:13:47.582 --> 00:13:50.924
My insights are now shaped by what I

00:13:50.965 --> 00:13:54.086
have learned since I last wrote and edited

00:13:54.147 --> 00:13:54.368
that,

00:13:54.408 --> 00:13:56.568
which probably the last edit pass would

00:13:56.589 --> 00:13:59.591
have been two to three years ago.

00:14:00.312 --> 00:14:02.393
And the amount that we've learned just in

00:14:02.413 --> 00:14:04.594
the last six months is so astonishing that

00:14:05.014 --> 00:14:08.336
I can bring those updated insights to you

00:14:08.716 --> 00:14:10.979
spontaneously as part of the Yahowah blog.

00:14:11.019 --> 00:14:13.620
But to read the text is wonderful.

00:14:13.639 --> 00:14:13.801
In fact,

00:14:13.841 --> 00:14:16.461
I was just thinking a matter of a

00:14:16.522 --> 00:14:17.283
half an hour ago.

00:14:18.423 --> 00:14:19.604
that when he always says,

00:14:19.644 --> 00:14:21.806
I want you to go to this blog

00:14:21.885 --> 00:14:24.187
format and I'll go here in a minute,

00:14:24.267 --> 00:14:26.308
return to my commentary on this text,

00:14:26.328 --> 00:14:27.048
which I think you'll,

00:14:27.068 --> 00:14:27.929
you'll find interesting.

00:14:27.950 --> 00:14:27.990
Uh,

00:14:28.929 --> 00:14:30.211
but when he always asked me to do

00:14:30.230 --> 00:14:33.933
this, it was in December of, uh, um,

00:14:34.594 --> 00:14:36.615
a full year plus ago, uh,

00:14:37.775 --> 00:14:40.418
to go from being a full-time translator

00:14:40.457 --> 00:14:42.698
and writer to a, uh, a vlogger.

00:14:42.739 --> 00:14:43.620
Um,

00:14:44.774 --> 00:14:44.955
You know,

00:14:44.975 --> 00:14:46.517
I was skeptical at first because,

00:14:46.758 --> 00:14:46.937
you know,

00:14:46.977 --> 00:14:50.482
this is a much more vulnerable experience.

00:14:50.623 --> 00:14:51.224
And, you know,

00:14:51.283 --> 00:14:54.830
my entire exposure with Yahowah prior to

00:14:54.870 --> 00:14:57.933
this had been reading what he had others

00:14:57.994 --> 00:14:58.335
write.

00:14:58.836 --> 00:14:59.316
And then...

00:15:02.018 --> 00:15:04.980
sharing what I was deducing from them in

00:15:05.019 --> 00:15:05.379
writing,

00:15:05.841 --> 00:15:08.982
recognizing that a written account is far

00:15:09.023 --> 00:15:09.783
more credible,

00:15:10.284 --> 00:15:14.207
that a written account has far greater

00:15:14.248 --> 00:15:14.967
longevity,

00:15:15.548 --> 00:15:18.571
and that God chose writing because it was

00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:19.751
the most reliable,

00:15:19.913 --> 00:15:22.914
consistent means of communication and the

00:15:22.955 --> 00:15:25.756
best way for him to demonstrate prophecy

00:15:25.817 --> 00:15:27.038
so that he could show that he

00:15:27.979 --> 00:15:28.359
In fact,

00:15:28.418 --> 00:15:30.379
inspired these words because he has a

00:15:30.440 --> 00:15:32.160
written legacy of things that would

00:15:32.201 --> 00:15:36.982
transpire centuries after he committed

00:15:37.023 --> 00:15:37.764
them to writing,

00:15:38.224 --> 00:15:40.924
proving the validity of his inspiration

00:15:41.085 --> 00:15:42.846
and that this is his testimony.

00:15:44.048 --> 00:15:45.490
And I like the fact that with a

00:15:45.529 --> 00:15:47.491
written word, you were empowered,

00:15:48.173 --> 00:15:49.855
which means that particularly if you're

00:15:49.875 --> 00:15:50.654
reading it online,

00:15:50.674 --> 00:15:52.116
you can go to YadaYah.com.

00:15:52.136 --> 00:15:54.600
All the books are free at YadaYah.com.

00:15:55.600 --> 00:16:00.907
You can copy and paste the genitive form

00:16:01.167 --> 00:16:02.268
of the Hebrew text.

00:16:02.349 --> 00:16:05.412
In this case, that opening word is,

00:16:06.032 --> 00:16:07.453
Not wa, therefore,

00:16:07.474 --> 00:16:09.615
but you have made him somewhat diminished,

00:16:09.655 --> 00:16:10.576
withholding something.

00:16:10.897 --> 00:16:14.740
It's from chaser and chaser huwʾma at.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:18.543
You can copy and paste each of those

00:16:18.582 --> 00:16:21.905
three words into the search engine of your

00:16:21.946 --> 00:16:25.708
choice and validate that my translation is

00:16:25.769 --> 00:16:26.169
accurate.

00:16:27.529 --> 00:16:28.010
So, you know,

00:16:28.030 --> 00:16:31.014
my only hope would be that you would

00:16:31.033 --> 00:16:33.736
be as thorough as I am,

00:16:33.777 --> 00:16:36.759
which means that I don't use one,

00:16:36.961 --> 00:16:37.520
but many.

00:16:37.541 --> 00:16:39.102
You know, if you just use one,

00:16:39.123 --> 00:16:40.585
you're probably going to be geared to

00:16:40.644 --> 00:16:42.326
Strong's since it's the most prevalent.

00:16:42.667 --> 00:16:44.928
But Strong's is written to justify the

00:16:44.969 --> 00:16:45.590
King James.

00:16:45.629 --> 00:16:47.572
So you have to be careful with it.

00:16:48.873 --> 00:16:51.695
And but there are when I'm doing this,

00:16:51.815 --> 00:16:54.135
I will examine ten to fifteen different

00:16:54.176 --> 00:16:57.097
lexicons and I will strip the word of

00:16:57.138 --> 00:16:59.580
its diacritical markings that the rabbis

00:16:59.659 --> 00:17:01.961
added in the eleventh century C.E.

00:17:02.421 --> 00:17:05.002
so that you can consider every.

00:17:05.682 --> 00:17:08.285
potential nuance that can be derived from

00:17:08.825 --> 00:17:11.707
the letters of each word as they were

00:17:11.727 --> 00:17:12.007
written.

00:17:12.488 --> 00:17:14.269
And then I will go to the pictographic

00:17:14.308 --> 00:17:15.309
characters and say,

00:17:15.809 --> 00:17:18.531
what do they have to say that would

00:17:18.571 --> 00:17:23.575
be illustrative in understanding the text?

00:17:23.976 --> 00:17:26.257
And I will also turn to the

00:17:27.518 --> 00:17:28.919
actionable root of each word,

00:17:29.659 --> 00:17:32.381
to analyze it as well so that you

00:17:32.441 --> 00:17:36.063
might know the intended meaning that was

00:17:36.143 --> 00:17:38.124
originally ascribed the term from God.

00:17:38.545 --> 00:17:39.765
So I would hope that you would be

00:17:39.826 --> 00:17:42.467
as thorough as I am, but you're welcome.

00:17:42.646 --> 00:17:45.449
And I think I know I'm the only

00:17:45.489 --> 00:17:46.529
translator ever.

00:17:47.289 --> 00:17:52.051
to give the reader the tools needed to

00:17:52.593 --> 00:17:55.334
validate or criticize my translations,

00:17:56.114 --> 00:17:58.315
doing so with a remarkably innovative

00:17:58.375 --> 00:18:00.777
style that heretofore had never existed

00:18:00.836 --> 00:18:03.597
previously, not only in its amplification,

00:18:03.938 --> 00:18:05.538
but also in its veracity.

00:18:07.807 --> 00:18:10.569
So having done this for all of that

00:18:10.651 --> 00:18:13.853
time and now asked to speak,

00:18:14.513 --> 00:18:15.714
I noticed that there were a lot of

00:18:15.775 --> 00:18:17.817
things that were different.

00:18:18.517 --> 00:18:20.939
One is that now that I was learning

00:18:21.019 --> 00:18:23.382
so much by going back all the text

00:18:23.541 --> 00:18:26.064
and having really the floodgates of

00:18:27.464 --> 00:18:29.906
understanding open to us over this past

00:18:29.946 --> 00:18:30.146
year,

00:18:30.952 --> 00:18:32.954
that if I had done what I had

00:18:32.994 --> 00:18:33.775
done in the past,

00:18:34.036 --> 00:18:37.057
which is to go back and update the

00:18:37.077 --> 00:18:39.000
books every time I learned something new

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.041
or wanted to edit something out that was

00:18:42.122 --> 00:18:44.523
now passe based upon a greater

00:18:44.565 --> 00:18:45.244
understanding,

00:18:46.205 --> 00:18:47.826
to go through thirty five books,

00:18:47.866 --> 00:18:50.490
twenty five thousand pages and make the

00:18:50.569 --> 00:18:52.631
series of changes based upon what we had

00:18:52.691 --> 00:18:55.073
learned would take two years.

00:18:55.814 --> 00:18:56.815
It's a long process.

00:18:57.234 --> 00:18:58.036
I was happy to do it.

00:18:58.076 --> 00:19:00.518
I wanted to have the books be as

00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:03.220
current and complete and accurate as

00:19:03.279 --> 00:19:03.701
possible.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:05.082
But it was a two-year endeavor.

00:19:05.561 --> 00:19:06.343
And in this case,

00:19:06.363 --> 00:19:08.003
we were learning so much at such a

00:19:08.044 --> 00:19:10.747
pace that it would be like painting the

00:19:10.787 --> 00:19:11.686
Golden Gate Bridge.

00:19:11.707 --> 00:19:13.048
You're going to have to have crews at

00:19:13.088 --> 00:19:13.949
both ends.

00:19:14.068 --> 00:19:15.770
And as soon as you finish,

00:19:15.790 --> 00:19:16.912
you go back the other way.

00:19:17.392 --> 00:19:18.053
We would never.

00:19:18.893 --> 00:19:21.694
get anything new written or anything new

00:19:21.734 --> 00:19:22.296
translated,

00:19:22.316 --> 00:19:25.077
because we'd just be improving what was

00:19:25.438 --> 00:19:26.218
already there.

00:19:26.759 --> 00:19:29.441
And so what I realized this morning is

00:19:29.480 --> 00:19:32.061
that not only does the Yahowah vlog and

00:19:32.102 --> 00:19:35.265
these live streams give us the opportunity

00:19:35.724 --> 00:19:38.967
to share with you the most recent

00:19:39.086 --> 00:19:39.587
insights,

00:19:39.627 --> 00:19:41.628
things that we may have only considered

00:19:42.209 --> 00:19:43.830
hours before the presentation.

00:19:44.790 --> 00:19:48.234
They also do something else that I just

00:19:48.255 --> 00:19:49.896
think is, well,

00:19:49.936 --> 00:19:51.518
this is another realization I thought was

00:19:51.538 --> 00:19:54.682
helpful, which is that even now,

00:19:54.801 --> 00:19:57.344
if I could just snap my fingers and

00:19:57.545 --> 00:20:00.607
instantly we had all the books, um,

00:20:01.268 --> 00:20:04.788
each of them right from an introduction to

00:20:04.828 --> 00:20:06.969
God, volume one, two, and three,

00:20:07.048 --> 00:20:10.430
and yada yada series one through nine,

00:20:10.710 --> 00:20:11.829
if they were all updated,

00:20:12.329 --> 00:20:14.611
even the observation series one through

00:20:14.651 --> 00:20:14.911
five,

00:20:15.770 --> 00:20:17.510
with the fullness of what we've come to

00:20:17.570 --> 00:20:18.971
understand,

00:20:18.991 --> 00:20:20.112
they wouldn't be understandable.

00:20:20.132 --> 00:20:25.492
You see, to some extent, as a reader,

00:20:26.586 --> 00:20:29.448
You need to come to this understanding as

00:20:29.508 --> 00:20:29.928
we did.

00:20:30.588 --> 00:20:32.308
You need to go through the process.

00:20:32.568 --> 00:20:35.971
You can't start with perfect and complete

00:20:36.490 --> 00:20:37.191
understanding.

00:20:39.011 --> 00:20:40.132
That's not how we learn.

00:20:40.532 --> 00:20:45.474
You don't start in kindergarten with

00:20:45.515 --> 00:20:46.095
calculus.

00:20:47.575 --> 00:20:48.454
You work up to it.

00:20:49.276 --> 00:20:52.298
And this is the same thing that's here.

00:20:52.999 --> 00:20:56.623
It's that if I'm able in the most

00:20:56.682 --> 00:20:57.363
recent books,

00:20:57.502 --> 00:20:59.065
and I am in the most recent books,

00:20:59.125 --> 00:21:01.146
but also in these programs,

00:21:02.387 --> 00:21:04.769
take you beyond where we have been so

00:21:04.789 --> 00:21:06.490
that you can show the growth,

00:21:06.590 --> 00:21:08.292
I can show the growth and understanding,

00:21:08.833 --> 00:21:08.993
then...

00:21:09.574 --> 00:21:11.835
that is a much better part of this

00:21:11.894 --> 00:21:13.476
process than otherwise.

00:21:13.496 --> 00:21:14.276
So, you know,

00:21:14.296 --> 00:21:15.396
I know that there are many covenant

00:21:15.436 --> 00:21:17.978
members who are reading books that I wrote

00:21:18.538 --> 00:21:20.179
five and ten years ago,

00:21:20.659 --> 00:21:23.740
and they are learning things that they

00:21:23.779 --> 00:21:24.921
never saw previously,

00:21:24.941 --> 00:21:26.020
because that's what we all do.

00:21:26.060 --> 00:21:27.741
The more we're exposed to Yah's testimony,

00:21:27.761 --> 00:21:29.022
the more we come to understand it.

00:21:29.343 --> 00:21:31.384
But they also know that there are things

00:21:31.423 --> 00:21:33.424
that I'm saying now that are way, way,

00:21:33.444 --> 00:21:35.665
way beyond what I might have interpreted

00:21:35.885 --> 00:21:36.625
back in the day.

00:21:37.296 --> 00:21:39.519
And that is all part of the process.

00:21:39.558 --> 00:21:42.222
And you should make this journey along

00:21:42.242 --> 00:21:43.884
with me as I made it,

00:21:43.964 --> 00:21:47.769
as opposed to just starting with calculus

00:21:47.829 --> 00:21:48.250
and saying, well,

00:21:48.269 --> 00:21:50.452
we'll just dispense with simple

00:21:50.512 --> 00:21:51.114
mathematics.

00:21:52.154 --> 00:21:53.017
It wouldn't be prudent.

00:21:55.239 --> 00:21:55.838
In this case,

00:21:56.659 --> 00:21:59.980
I'm very comfortable in taking you beyond

00:22:00.779 --> 00:22:02.220
where I have been previously.

00:22:02.560 --> 00:22:03.701
So this reads, therefore,

00:22:04.141 --> 00:22:06.161
so you have made, he's speaking to Yahowah,

00:22:06.181 --> 00:22:08.241
this is Dowd, his beloved son.

00:22:08.662 --> 00:22:11.162
You have made him, mankind,

00:22:12.163 --> 00:22:12.942
somewhat diminished,

00:22:13.323 --> 00:22:14.903
withholding something from you.

00:22:15.423 --> 00:22:16.343
See,

00:22:17.023 --> 00:22:18.604
more than just a little bit diminished.

00:22:19.344 --> 00:22:21.405
where God says that he created us in

00:22:21.445 --> 00:22:21.925
his image.

00:22:22.425 --> 00:22:23.787
The word that he used for image,

00:22:23.807 --> 00:22:25.008
and I've shared this previously,

00:22:26.189 --> 00:22:31.933
is like comparing a blueprint to a

00:22:31.973 --> 00:22:32.354
building.

00:22:33.734 --> 00:22:36.156
The blueprint tells the builder how to

00:22:36.196 --> 00:22:36.936
build the building.

00:22:38.325 --> 00:22:40.205
But you can roll the blueprint up.

00:22:40.425 --> 00:22:41.246
Here's this house.

00:22:41.567 --> 00:22:43.667
I can roll up the entire blueprint for

00:22:43.708 --> 00:22:46.429
this house and, you know,

00:22:46.489 --> 00:22:47.630
twenty sheets of paper.

00:22:47.730 --> 00:22:48.190
And, you know,

00:22:48.230 --> 00:22:49.810
it comes into a nice little roll and

00:22:50.191 --> 00:22:51.211
you can put it in your hand.

00:22:51.271 --> 00:22:53.813
And and yet that doesn't have the

00:22:53.853 --> 00:22:55.794
substance of one of the stones that I

00:22:55.834 --> 00:22:58.055
put on the wall for this house,

00:22:58.414 --> 00:23:00.976
much less the dimensionality of this whole

00:23:01.036 --> 00:23:01.336
thing.

00:23:01.376 --> 00:23:01.676
You know,

00:23:01.757 --> 00:23:04.097
as it as it goes from one corner

00:23:04.157 --> 00:23:06.459
to another and builds up from the the

00:23:06.479 --> 00:23:07.720
ground to the ceiling.

00:23:08.180 --> 00:23:09.681
the top of the roof.

00:23:10.902 --> 00:23:14.323
There is to go from two dimensions,

00:23:14.343 --> 00:23:15.523
which is what a blueprint is,

00:23:15.784 --> 00:23:17.444
to three dimensions is actually an

00:23:17.605 --> 00:23:20.686
infinite increase.

00:23:20.767 --> 00:23:21.587
And in our case,

00:23:21.988 --> 00:23:23.828
Yahowah created us in three dimensions.

00:23:25.886 --> 00:23:27.406
stuck in the fourth dimension,

00:23:27.426 --> 00:23:28.647
the ordinary flow of time.

00:23:29.268 --> 00:23:31.448
When he is liberated, not only in time,

00:23:31.488 --> 00:23:33.269
the fourth dimension, but also the fifth,

00:23:33.288 --> 00:23:35.628
the sixth dimension as well.

00:23:36.209 --> 00:23:37.650
And I think that the universe,

00:23:37.690 --> 00:23:41.390
based upon what we perceive of it as

00:23:41.470 --> 00:23:43.891
the five percent that we can recognize,

00:23:43.951 --> 00:23:45.431
and all we can do is the math,

00:23:45.451 --> 00:23:46.971
but we have no understanding of what the

00:23:47.010 --> 00:23:49.152
repulsive force is or the attractive force

00:23:49.172 --> 00:23:51.392
that we call dark energy and dark matter,

00:23:52.172 --> 00:23:53.752
that the universe is actually six

00:23:53.792 --> 00:23:54.272
dimensions.

00:23:55.479 --> 00:23:57.400
And this would play somewhat into what

00:23:57.660 --> 00:23:58.861
they call string theory.

00:24:00.181 --> 00:24:01.382
And that Yahowah,

00:24:01.422 --> 00:24:03.303
to create a six dimensional universe must

00:24:03.323 --> 00:24:04.983
be seven dimensions minimally.

00:24:05.824 --> 00:24:07.484
You have to be a dimension beyond that

00:24:07.505 --> 00:24:10.346
which you create to create something of

00:24:10.567 --> 00:24:11.386
this magnitude.

00:24:11.727 --> 00:24:12.186
Otherwise,

00:24:12.227 --> 00:24:14.868
what you're doing is rearranging what

00:24:14.909 --> 00:24:15.648
already exists.

00:24:15.689 --> 00:24:17.670
Like when I took the blueprint that I

00:24:17.710 --> 00:24:20.891
drew for this house and then built the

00:24:20.951 --> 00:24:22.612
house based upon that blueprint,

00:24:22.991 --> 00:24:24.813
I had to use materials that already

00:24:24.873 --> 00:24:25.314
existed.

00:24:25.394 --> 00:24:28.134
I just repurposed those materials,

00:24:28.194 --> 00:24:29.035
if you will,

00:24:29.855 --> 00:24:31.557
to create this house that is very

00:24:31.656 --> 00:24:32.156
different

00:24:32.596 --> 00:24:36.119
than creating a universe out of nothing,

00:24:36.840 --> 00:24:38.662
the light and the energy and the matter

00:24:38.721 --> 00:24:40.163
and all of those sorts of things,

00:24:40.242 --> 00:24:40.844
and then life.

00:24:41.624 --> 00:24:42.704
So it's a very different thing.

00:24:42.904 --> 00:24:45.488
And in the case of God,

00:24:45.867 --> 00:24:48.470
when he gave humankind a Neshamah,

00:24:48.509 --> 00:24:49.490
which is a conscience,

00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:50.991
the ability to reason,

00:24:51.031 --> 00:24:52.512
to know the difference between right and

00:24:52.553 --> 00:24:53.433
wrong, good and bad,

00:24:53.574 --> 00:24:54.734
that which is productive and

00:24:54.835 --> 00:24:55.556
counterproductive.

00:24:56.836 --> 00:25:00.777
He created us such that we had the

00:25:00.836 --> 00:25:04.238
capacity to know him, to think like him,

00:25:05.137 --> 00:25:06.637
to respond to him,

00:25:06.778 --> 00:25:09.618
to even be trusted by him with that

00:25:09.679 --> 00:25:10.179
conscience.

00:25:10.638 --> 00:25:13.159
But it still meant that we are a

00:25:13.239 --> 00:25:14.619
huge distance from him.

